This paper deals with preference aggregation, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The problem of recognizing single-peakedness is a classic problem in social choice theory, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with decision-making processes (cs.DS).
